        <h2>What is the difference between Gynecology and obstetrics?</h2>
        <ul class="ul">
            <p>Gynecology and Obstetrics are twin subjects that are connected with the female.</p><br>
            <p>Obstetrics addresses pregnancy and its related procedures and disorders, including deliveries.</p><br>
            <p>On the other hand, gynecology involves treating the female reproductive system, the women who are not pregnant, including Chronic pain and sexually transmitted infections. </p><br>
            <p>Gynecology encompasses both medicines as well as surgical fields. Often, gynecological illnesses need hormonal treatment while, other pharmacological management, fibroids, and cancer needed surgical removal. </p><br>
            <p>OB-GYN is a specialist who has broad experience in obstetrics and gynecology. OB-GYN offers treatment for the services including STI Testing, pelvic exams, ultrasounds, pap smears, and blood work. They also help women to answer their queries related to sex, pregnancy, infertility, reproductive health, and many others. </p><br>
            <p>An Overview of Treatment and Procedures from the Best Gynecology Hospital in Jaipur Related to Gynecology and Obstetrics</p><br>
            <p>Gynecology and obstetrics are the medical and surgical specialties that focus on the research and treatment of women’s health issues, respectively. Both fields are closely related, and many healthcare providers practice both gynecology and obstetrics.</p><br>
            <p>Common gynecological disorders include pelvic inflammatory disease, uterine fibroids, endometriosis, and ovarian cysts. Gynecologists may also provide care for pregnant women, including prenatal and postnatal care.</p><br>
            <p>Obstetric disorders include pregnancy-related conditions such as preterm labor, gestational diabetes, and preeclampsia. Obstetricians may also provide care for women who are experiencing complications during childbirth.</p><br>
            <p>Gynecologists and obstetricians often work together to provide comprehensive care for women. In some cases, a woman may see a gynecologist for her regular care and an obstetrician for her prenatal and postnatal care.</p><br>
            
        </div>
